          "statement": "Before a commit-equivalent approval boundary, changed design documents must be checked for required sections such as Overview, Player Fantasy, Detailed Rules, Formulas, Edge Cases, Dependencies, Tuning Knobs, and Acceptance Criteria; when native lifecycle hooks are unavailable, preserve this intent through protocol_downgrade into canonical pre-commit validation stages rather than dropping the check.",
          "severity": "warning",
          "failure_mode": "warn"
        },
        {
          "code": "POL_VALIDATE_STRUCTURED_DATA_INTEGRITY",
          "statement": "Machine-readable project data must be syntactically valid before the commit-equivalent action proceeds; invalid structured data blocks progression, and runtimes without native commit interception must run the validation through an external_runner so the blocking guarantee remains explicit.",
          "severity": "error",
          "failure_mode": "block"
        },
        {
          "code": "POL_WARN_ON_ACTIONABLE_CODE_QUALITY_SIGNALS",
          "statement": "Implementation changes should surface actionable warnings for obvious anti-patterns such as unowned TODO or FIXME markers and hardcoded gameplay balance values that belong in data, with warnings preserved even when enforcement is routed through protocol_downgrade or external_runner fallback paths.",
          "severity": "warning",
          "failure_mode": "warn"
        },
        {
          "code": "POL_REQUIRE_VISIBLE_FALLBACK_HANDLING",
          "statement": "If a target runtime cannot express native pre-commit validation hooks, the harness must route commit-validation intent to external_runner or protocol_downgrade handling and must not silently omit the validation boundary.",
          "severity": "error",
          "failure_mode": "fallback"
        }
      ]
    },
